To use the semantic parsing, first make sure you have ".env" in your root library. It should be documented as follows.

API_KEY=ABCD1234
CLIENT_ID=EFGH5678
CLIENT_SECRET=WXYZ9999

You also have to make sure you are either on the Wash U network or connected to the VPN.
Then, open SemanticParsing.py and press run!
One note on the system: For now, semanticparsing does not support Atomic Simulated Environment.
If the parsing module picks ASE, just say no and specify pymatgen in the prompt.
For now, the full output (including cost, etc) is printed in the terminal, the data is written in json format
to data.json, and the program terminates. The data.json file will be overwritten so if you want to use it make sure to
save the work in a differently named file!